Laptop specs:
1.64 bit
2.Lenovo G510
3.System Information > BIOS mode > UEFI

Requirements

1. windows 10
2. 8GB+ pendrive
3. 20GB+ free space

Step 1.
Download ubuntu 20.04 

Step 2.
write iso image to PD

Step 3 : create partition for Ubuntu 
1.search : disk partitions
2.shrink any of the drive's (lets say C/)
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/49392224/82070820-e8310480-96f2-11ea-8237-fd7caf72e72f.png)
Total size before shrink in MB : 215112
Size of Available shrink space in MB : 38012
Enter the amount of space to shrink in MB : 38021
Total size after shrink in MB : 177091
3.But I have 83.42GB unallocated space

Step 4: try install
1.turn off Laptop
2.connect USB with Ubuntu iso image
2.start using recovery key
3.enter BIOS > install ubuntu
4.do ubuntu installation steps : choose keyboard, country, partition etc


Uninstall ubuntu from Dual Boot
Step 1.remove ubuntu

Step 2.remove grub bootloader
1.enter windows menu
  press shift key (keep it pressed) > restart Laptop > windows menu
  
  windows menu : Continue, Trouble Shoot, Turn off your PC
  
  Trouble shoot > Advance options > Command prompt > select account (gaurav7x7) > enter password 
  
  On command prompt :
  X:\Sources>bootrec /fixmbr
  
  X:\Sources>bootrec /fixboot
  
  X:\Sources>bootrec /scanos











